Exaggerate: The claim may be exaggerating the age of the average minimum wage worker by stating that they are 35 years old.
Lack enough support: The claim may lack enough support as it does not provide any evidence or data to back up the statement.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the average minimum wage worker is 35 years old without providing any justification or explanation for this assumption.
Exist alternative explanation: There may be alternative explanations for the age of minimum wage workers that are not mentioned or explored in the claim.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that the study used by the White House included workers earning up to $11.10, not just those earning the minimum wage.
